Name: Chaos Rest
Description: Whenever you take a short rest, roll thrice on the Choas Rest table. Each of the regional effects occur around you while you rest.

Name: Fivehead
Description: 5 times per Long Rest when you fail a saving throw you may add 1d4 to the roll, possibly turning it into a success.

Name: Chaotic Spellcasting
Description: Instead of casting a specific spell you can also choose to roll a die. Pick a spell level and count how many spells of that level you have prepared that take an action to cast. Roll a die with that many faces and the spell that it lands on gets cast. The spell is cast as if it was cast with a spellslot level one higher than the one used.

Name: Dyslectik Spellcasting
Description: Once per long rest when you cast a spell, you may change one letter of the spell, and the effect accordingly. The power of the spell remains approximately the same.

Name: Chromatic Snack Summoner
Description:
Once per long rest you can cast Summon Beast at a level equal to your proficiency bonus. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for this spell. The type of beast it summons depends on the Chromatic type you associate with as seen in the Snack Summon table
When you cast the spell in this way it requires no components. If you kill the beast you regain a number of hit points equal to 5 times your proficiency bonus. Once you attack the beast it is no longer an ally and will fight back, but wonâ€™t run. 
You may also cast the spell in the regular way with any spell slots you have yourself.

Name: Improved Elemental Spellcasting
Description: Depending on your subrace you gain access to additional spells. You may cast these spells once per long rest and you use the same spellcasting ability as your other racial spells. You can also cast them with any spell slots of the appropriate level. If you have the Elemental Chaos or Mark of Tiamat Orenth Trait you may also choose the Chaos option. Improved Elemental Spells

Name: Power from Wealth
Description: For every 500 gp in gold coins you have on you (that is part of your personal wealth and not shared with anyone) during a long rest your current and maximum hit points increase by 1 to a maximum of twice your original maximum hp. This benefit lasts until the end of your next long rest.

Name: Fire born of the Sun
Description: You may pick a tier 3 Cosmic (Sun) Orenth trait. Additionally this trait counts as a tier 3 Cosmic Orenth trait for the purpose of gaining access to further orenth traits.

Name: Conductivity
Description: As an action point towards a willing creature within 100 feet of you that has a Lightning Orenth trait. You cast Lightning Bolt in their direction, using Wisdom as your spellcasting ability, but the spell ends at their location and they aren't affected. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Acidous Weakness
Description: Whenever you take slashing damage you may deal acid damage equal to twice your level to any creature of your choice within 10 feet of you.

Name: Merciless Strikes
Description: Whenever you hit a prone, unconscious or paralyzed creature with a weapon attack, you may deal additional fire damage to them equal to your Wisdom modifier.

Name: Flying Charge
Description: Choose a weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Reach property. For every 10 feet you move straight toward a creature before hitting it with an attack with this weapon, the target takes an extra 1d6 damage.

Name: Frozen Winds
Description: Twice per turn when you push a creature you may deal 1d4 cold damage to the creature for every 10 feet you push them

Name: Relentless
Description: Whenever you hit with an attack roll you may choose to make an additional attack. You can keep making additional attacks until you miss with an attack roll, but each attack gets a cumulative -2 penalty to the attack roll. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier and regain all uses at the end of a long rest.

Name: Flyby
Description: When you make a melee attack against a creature while flying, you don't provoke opportunity attacks from that creature for the rest of the turn, whether you hit or not.

Name: Elemental Spellcasting
Prerequisite: A tier 2 fire, lightning, wood, water or cold orenth trait
Description: Whenever you cast a spell that deals elemental damage you can choose to change the damage type to the damage type associated with your previous orenth trait. Whenever you cast a spell that deals the same damage as your previously chosen orenth trait you may deal an additional 1d6 damage of that type.

Name: Chromatic Resistance
Description: You gain resistance to fire, lightning, poison, acid or cold damage. Additionally, once on your turn you may deal additional damage equal to your proficiency bonus when you hit with an attack roll. The type of damage is the same as the one you have resistance to.

Name: Jumping Spark
Description: You gain the benefits of the Cleave Orenth trait. Before you make the second attack you may move 10 feet without provoking opportunity attacks or using your movement. You must end this movement in a place where you can reach your second target.

Name: Jumping Lightning
Description: You may move up to 15 feet whenever you use your Jumping Charge ability. Additionally, whenever you cleave attack hits you may move again and strike a different target.

Name: Synced Spellcasting
Description: When a creature casts a spell within 60 feet of you that you have prepared, you can use your reaction to expend a spell slot to cast the same spell. The spell slot must be of the same or lower level as the triggering spell.

Name: Interrupted Teleport
Description: As a reaction to a creature teleporting within 60 feet of you can make an opposed Intelligence (Arcana) check against the teleporter. On a success you interrupt their teleport, causing them to only travel half the distance they intended to and taking 1d6 force damage for every 10 feet they intended to teleport (to a maximum number of dice equal to your level). On a success, they teleport successfully and only take half damage. You may use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Eldritch Doom
Description: When you deal damage to a creature you can Doom them. While they are Doomed they take an additional 1d4 damage whenever they take damage. You may use this feature once per long rest.

Name: Swarm in disguise
Description: You can occupy another creature's space and vice versa, and you can move through any opening large enough for a Tiny creature. You become resistant to bludgeoning, piercing and slashing damage. However, whenever you regain hit points or gain temporary hit points you only get half.

Name: Horrific Jaw
Prerequisite: Ability to make a Bite attack
Description: You unhinge your jaw and attempt to swallow a creature whole. When you hit a creature of equal or smaller size than you with a bite attack, you may attempt to swallow it whole. It must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw (DC = 8+ your proficiency bonus + your Constitution modifier). On a failure, it gets swallowed into a pocket dimension, which it can attempt to escape at the end of each of its turns by repeating the saving throw, if it succeeds on a consequent turn it appears in an unoccupied space within 5 feet you. On a success, nothing happens. You may use this feature a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Incomprehendable Mind
Description: You become immune to psychic damage.

Name: Demiplanar Stomach
Description: Your mouth functions as a bag of holding.

Name: Heat Stroke
Description: As an action you can channel the exhaustive heat of the sun. For the next minute any creature of your choice that starts its turn within 10 feet of you must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC = 8+your Proficiency Bonus + your Constitution modifier). On a failure they gain a exhaustion levels equal to your proficiency bonus that while they are within 10 feet of you and your aura remains. On a success they become immune to the effect for the next hour. You may use this feature a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Burning Touch
Description: Once per turn when you hit with an unarmed strike you may deal fire damage to the creature equal to your Proficiency bonus. Additionally whenever a creature starts its turn being grappled they also take fire damage equal to your Proficiency bonus.

Name: Burned Memories of the Amnizu
Description: Once per long rest you may cast Modify Memory using Charisma as your spellcasting ability. On a successful save the creature takes fire damage equal to twice your level.

Name: Little sustenance needed
Description: You can drink from a potion twice and get the full effect both times. Additionally you only need to drink and eat half as much.

Name: Shroud of the Wilderness
Description: While you are in an area that is lightly obscured, you can Hide as a bonus action even if you are being directly observed.

Name: Goblin Magic
Description: You are in tune with your Fey ancestry. You learn the Prestidigitation cantrip. In addition, once per turn when you hit a creature with a spell attack you can do 2d6 extra damage if an ally is within 5 feet of the target.

Name: Efficiency of the Small
Description: You have become efficient with managing your movements in battle. As a bonus action you can select two options from your Nimble Escape feature at the same time. If you have the Cunning Action feature you can also pick one of those options.

Name: Goblin Ferocity
Description: Your feral nature allows you to move faster. As a bonus action you can move up to your speed to a target. If you move 30 feet in a straight line you are allowed to make a weapon attack or unarmed strike as part of the Bonus Action. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all uses after you finish a Long Rest.

Name: Faster than your Shadow
Description: You may make an opportunity attack against a creature moved forcefully.

Name: Opportunity of Many
Description: Choose a weapon you are proficient with that has the Two-Handed property. While flanking an opponent you get advantage on the attack roll when wielding this weapon.

Name: Master Fey Bargainer
Description: Whenever you roll with advantage you roll three dice and take the highest one. Whenever you roll with disadvantage you roll three dice and the lowest one.

Name: Improved Fey Steps
Description: You have become more adept at using your Fey Steps casually. When you use your bonus action for Fey Steps you donâ€™t provoke attacks of opportunity.

Name: Anti Parallel Timelines
Description: Once per long rest as a reaction to taking damage you take no damage and gain a number of temporary hit points equal to the damage dealt instead.

Name: Illusory Duplicates
Description: At the start of your turn you may choose to create an illusory duplicate of yourself. Both versions of you can move up to your movement speed, but you share your action and bonus action. If you have the Extra Attack ability you can split the extra attack(s) between your two versions. At the end of your turn you decide which one is the real you and the duplicate dissapears. Both versions of you share the same hp pool, so whenever one takes damage the other takes the same damage.

Name: Ruby Rest
Description: Whenever you take a short rest you may choose two Gem Rest Orenth effects that remain active during your rest.

Name: Spooky Ghost Boy
Description: Once per long rest you get a flying speed equal to your walking speed for the next minute, you can hover and you can move through creatures but not end your turn inside of them.

Name: Old habits didn't die
Description: Whenever you make an ability check have proficiency with you may choose to not roll and take 10 instead. You may do this a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and regain all uses after a Long Rest.

Name: Sent with a mission from Sardior
Description: You are so focused on your task given to you by Sardior you can't be distracted easily. You have advantage on Constitution saving throws made to maintain concentration and saving throws to avoid being charmed.

Name: Dragonborn of Sardior
Description: You count as every type of gem dragonborn for the sake of Orenth Prerequisites, and you do not need to meet any Sardior piety prerequisite. Additionally, you may pick a tier 2 Orenth trait

Name: Echolocation
Description: You have blindsight out to 30 feet while you aren't deafened. Within that range, you can effectively see anything that isn't behind total cover, even if you're blinded or in darkness. Moreover, you can see an invisible creature within that range, unless the creature successfully hides from you.

Name: Shell Shock
Description: Whenever you deal thunder damage to a creature you may force them to make a Constitution saving throw (DC=8+your your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier). On a a failure they lose any bonus they had to their armour class due to natural armour until the end of your next turn. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and regain all uses after you finish a Long Rest

Name: Temporary Ressurection
Description: When you reduce a creature to 0 hit points you may use your reaction to keep its corpse under your temporary control. The creature regains 1 hit point and becomes charmed by you until the end of your next turn. While charmed you can give it commands that it must obey (no action from you required). You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and regain all uses at the end of a long rest.

Name: Drain its life
Description: You gain the benefits of the Sap Orenth trait. After you use your Sap Orenth trait the creature only deals half damage on the next attack that hits.

Name: Psionic Cleave
Description: You get the benefits of the Cleave Orenth trait. Additionally, wheneveryou make the second attack, the second creature must be within 10 feet of the original but not necessarilily within your reach.

Name: Transfer of Kinetic Energy
Description: You gain the benefits of the Slow Orenth trait. Additionally, whenever you reduce a creature's speed your own speed increases by 10 feet until the end of your turn.

Name: Elegant Fighting
Description: Pick one weapon that you have proficiency with that lacks the Finesse trait. This weapon is now considered a Finesse weapon when you wield it.

Name: Mastery over Body and Mind
Description: You gain the benefits of the Elegant Fighting Orenth trait. Additionally, you may use your Intelligence instead of your Strength or Dexterity for attack and damage rolls when fighting with a Finesse weapon.

Name: Cosmic Orenth Transmuter
Description: As an action you can touch an aberration or fiend that has been killed within the last minute. It must have a minimum CR of 7. Over the course of the next hour the Cosmic Orenth of the creature is captured inside a newly created Gem Stalker of an appropriate colour. This Gem Stalker remains under your control for the next week, after which it learns the location of the nearest Gem Dragon that matches its type and comes under their control instead. You may only create a Gem Stalker in this way when you have none under your control.

Name: Gem Snack Summoner
Description:
Once per long rest you can cast Summon Beast at a level equal to your proficiency bonus. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for this spell. The type of beast it summons depends on the Gem type you associate with as seen in the Snack Summon table
When you cast the spell in this way it requires no components. If you kill the beast you regain a number of hit points equal to 5 times your proficiency bonus. Once you attack the beast it is no longer an ally and will fight back, but wonâ€™t run. 
You may also cast the spell in the regular way with any spell slots you have yourself.

Name: Arcane Connection
Description: You can cast any spell you can cast once per long rest because of a racial trait, once per short rest instead.

Name: Gem Resistance
Description: You gain resistance to one of the following pairs of damage types: force and psychic, thunder and lightning, psychic and fire, necrotic and acid, or cold and radiant damage. Additionally, whenever someone rolls for damage within 30 feet of you you may use your reaction to change the damage type to one of the ones you gained resistance to from this trait. You may use this reaction a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and regain all uses at the end of a Long Rest.

Name: Induced Gravity
Description: You gain the benefits of the Slow Orenth trait. Additionally, any creature of your choice within 10 feet of the creature you slowed also has its speed reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn.

Name: Friendly Strikes
Prerequisite: Exclusive, a Tier 1 Fey Orenth trait.
Description: You gain the benefits of the Sap Orenth trait. Additionally, whenever you hit a creature you may choose to charm them instead. They must make a Wisdom saving throw (DC = 8+your proficiency bonus+your Intelligence modifier). On a failed save they become charmed by you until the start of your next turn. On a successful save nothing happens (and they also don't gain disadvantage on their next attack against you). You may use this feature a number of times equal to your Intelligence modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Ruby Spellcasting
Prerequisite: 10+ piety with Sardior and a Gem Spellcasting Orenth trait.
Description: Whenever you use your Gem Spellcasting Orenth trait you may also regain a 2nd level spellslot.

Name: Induced Intoxication
Description: The alcohol finally kicks in. As a bonus action you can gain the following effects. For the next hour, you have disadvantage on Intelligence and Wisdom ability checks and saving throws. Additionally, your current hit points and hit point maximum increase by an amount equal to your level, and you gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your constitution modifier at the start of each of your turns. It automatically activates when you drop to 0 hit points, but then you can't use it again until the end of your next long rest. You may use this ability once per Short Rest as long as you had alcohol during the short rest.

Name: Iron Skin
Description: Your skin hardens like iron, giving you resistance to bludgeoning, piercing or slashing damage.

Name: Grounded
Description: As a reaction you can become immune to lightning damage until the end of your next turn. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all uses at the end of a Long Rest.

Name: Body Slam
Description: While grappling a creature you may use the creature as a weapon. Your unarmed strikes against other creatures deal an additional 1d4 bludgeoning damage and whenever you hit a creature the creature you are grappling also takes 1d4 bludgeoning damage.

Name: It's the little things that count
Description: You may pick 3 tier 1 Orenth traits of any type. These traits count as Ingens Orenth traits for you.

Name: Ooblek Armor
Description: Whenever you take damage you may use your reaction to increase your AC by the number of damage dice dealt until the end of your next turn.

Name: Constricted Constrict
Description: After you grapple a creature you may attempt to grapple the creature again, restraining the creature on a success. If the creature escapes your grapple the restrained condition also ends.

Name: Rapid Adaptation
Description: As a reaction to taking damage you can become resistant to that damage until the end of your next turn. You may use this reaction a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier and regain all uses at the end of a Long Rest

Name: Charge
Description: Choose a weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Heavy and Reach property. If you move at least 20 feet straight toward a creature before hitting it with an attack with this weapon, the target takes an extra 1d12 damage and must make a Strength saving throw with a DC equal to 8 + your Proficiency Bonus + the ability modifier you used to make the attack roll. On a failure, the target falls prone.

Name: Graze
Description: Choose a melee weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Heavy property. If your attack roll with this weapon misses a creature, you can deal damage to that creature equal to the ability modifier you used to make the attack roll. This damage is the same type dealt by the weapon, and the damage canâ€™t be increased in any way, other than increasing the ability modifier.

Name: Nick
Description:
Choose a weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Light property, your Unarmed Strike if you have the Martial Arts feature or a Double Bladed Scimitar if you have the Revenant Blade Feat. When you make the extra attack of the Light property, you can make it as part of the Attack action, instead of as a Bonus Action. You can still make this extra attack only once per turn. 
If you have the Martial Arts feature you can instead make an unarmed strike as part of the action. If you use the Flurry of Blows feature you can spend 1 ki to make an additional unarmed strike as a bonus action.

Name: Push
Description: Choose a weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Heavy, Two-Handed or Versatile Property. If you hit a creature with this weapon, you may push them up to 10 feet away from you horizontally, if it is no more than one size larger than you.

Name: Topple
Description: Choose a weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Heavy, Reach or Versatile property. Once per turn when you hit a creature no more than one size larger than you with this weapon, you can force the creature to make a Strength saving throw with a DC equal to 8 + your Proficiency Bonus + the ability modifier you used to make the attack roll. On a failed save, the creature has the Prone condition.

Name: Vex
Description: Choose a weapon that you have proficiency with that has the Ammunition, Finesse, or Light property. If you hit a creature with this weapon and deal damage to the creature, you have Advantage on your next attack roll against that creature before the end of your next turn.

Name: Deadliest Weapon
Description: You gain a tier 2 Orenth trait with the Weapon Mastery subtype. Additionally, you may apply two different Orenth traits with the Exclusive prerequisite to the same weapon.

Name: Bounce
Description: You get the benefits of the Push Orenth trait, but instead of pushing the creature, you can decide to push yourself 10 feet in a direction of your choice instead. This movement does not provoke opportunity attacks.

Name: Shield and Sword
Description: You get the benefits of the Flex Orenth trait. Additionally, while wearing a shield and using the weapon from your Flex Orenth trait you may add the shield's AC to the damage you deal with your Flex weapon.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Graze
Description: Whenever you graze a creature you may apply damage bonuses such as sneak attack, smites and similar abilities that would trigger on a hit.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Close Quarters Combat
Description: The extra attack from your Close Quarters Combat Orenth trait no longer requires your bonus action or reaction, but you may still only use them once per turn.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Charge
Description: You only need to move 10 feet to use your Charge Orenth trait ability and the extra damage you deal increases to 2d12.

Name: Weapon Masterded: Nick
Description: Whenever you use your Nick Orenth trait you can make two additional attacks instead of one. However, one of the attacks must deal just the weapon damage with no modifiers applied.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Strangle
Description: After you successfully grapple a creature with your Strangle Orenth Trait they gain disadvantage on Constitution saving throws for the next minute.

Name: 1damage1dice
Description: You gain the benefits of the Flex Orenth trait. Additionally, while wielding the weapon with two hands the damage die increases by one.

Name: Weapon Mastered: Bloody Wound
Description: The damage die for the bleeding damage becomes1d6. Additionally the DC for the medicine check becomes 8+your proficiency bonus + the ability used for the weapon attack.

Name: Mixed Human Heritage
Description: You may pick one racial feat for which you don't meet the requirements that gives you an ability score improvement. You don't gain the ability score improvement from the feat.

Name: The Stubbornest
Description: Whenever you fail a saving throw you may choose to succeed it instead. You may use this ability a number of times equal to the amount of Orenth traits you have with stubborn in them and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Adaptive Feats
Description: Whenever you finish a long rest you may choose one feat of your choice and swap it out for a different one. You must meet the requirements for the replacement feat.

Name: Jack
Description: You gain a +1 bonus to ability checks you dont have proficiency in.

Name: Stunning Question
Description: You pose such a profound philosophical question that you stun a creature. Once per Long rest, as an action, you can target a creature that can hear you and that you share a language with. They must succeed on an Intelligence saving throw (DC = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier). On a failure, they become stunned for one minute. They may repeat the saving throw at the start of their turns, ending the effect on a success.

Name: Endurance Fighting
Description: Whenever you deal damage to a creature, and afterwards the creature has more hit points than you, you gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your Constitution modifier.

Name: Shared Resistance
Description: Any creature of your choice within 15 feet of you shares any resistance you have.

Name: Saving expert
Description: You may get expertise in saving throws.

Name: Bronze Saviour
Description: Whenever a creature within 60 feet of you is about to hit a creature other than you, you may use your reaction to protect them before being struck down. You can give them a bonus to their AC equal to your Charisma modifier until the end of your next turn. You may use this ability a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier, and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Purposeful Knight
Description: You designate a creature that needs to be vanquished as a Bonus Action. Until it is dead or a minute has passed you gain hit points equal to your Charisma modifier at the start of each of your turns you start within 10 feet of them. You may use this ability once per Long Rest.

Name: Platinum Rest
Description: Whenever you take a short rest you may choose two Metallic rest Orenth effects that remain active during your rest.

Name: Frozen Strikes
Description: You get the benefits of the Slow Orenth trait, with the following change: There is no more limit to how much you can decrease a creature's speed.

Name: Exalting Breath
Description: Whenever you use your breath weapon, you may choose any creature in the area that regains hit points equal to the damage dealt, instead of taking damage.

Name: No Escape
Description: As a reaction to a creature leaving your reach you can choose to move with them as far as your movement allows.

Name: Hands of Supreme Healing
Description: You may roll d12s instead of d8s whenever you use your Healing Hands ability. Additionally you can use this trait thrice per short rest instead of once per long rest.

Name: Celestial Body
Description: You become immune to the effects of curses that can be removed with the remove curse spell.

Name: Metallic Resistance
Description: You gain resistance to fire, cold, lightning, acid or radiant damage. Additionally, whenever you take this type of damage, the creature that dealt the damage takes the same damage.

Name: Shoveling Hands
Prerequisite: Kobold with ancestry of a dragon that can dig
Description: Like the dragon you take after, youâ€™ve got a knack for digging. You get a burrow speed equal to half your walking speed.

Name: Flexible Orenth
Description: You may use any ability score to determine your save DC and number of times you can use an orenth trait. You also gain an additional use for any trait that recharges after a long rest.

Name: Dissuading Words
Description: You gain the benefits of the Sap Orenth trait. Additionally after you hit a creature they also have disadvantage on their next Wisdom Saving Throw.

Name: School Mastered: Enchantment
Prerequisite: Spell mastery with an Enchantment school spell.
Description: Creatures no longer have advantage on saving throws against your enchantment spells if you are currently fighting them.

Name: Summer Solstice
Description: The summer solstice marks the longest day of the year, but also the day where the night start to grow longer. Over the course of a round keep track of the total number of hit points that were regained. For the purposes of this trait a round starts after your turn has ended. On your turn, when you deal damage to a creature you may deal additional radiant damage equal to the amount of hit points regained. You may use this trait a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier, and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Winter Solstice
Description: The Winter solstice marks the shortest day and longest night of the year, but also the day that the nights start to become shorter again. Over the course of a round keep track of the number of damage dice that were rolled. For the purposes of this trait a round starts after your turn has ended. On your turn, you may use your bonus action to heal a creature within 60 feet of you for a number of hit points equal to that amount. You may use this trait a number of times equal to your Constitution modifier and regain all uses after a long rest.

Name: Giving Thanks
Description: Whenever another creature gives you hitpoints, you may use your reaction to thank them. Until the end of their next turn they gain advantage on d20 checks. You may use this ability once per short rest.

Name: Quick Rebuttal
Description: You gain the benefits of the Lock Blades Orenth trait. Additionally, whenever you beat the attacker's attack roll by more than 5 you may deal damage to them equal to the ability score modifier used to parry the attack. The damage type is that of your weapon.
